{
  "texts": [
    "To ensure the responsible and effective use of LLMs in diagnostic medicine, the following considerations should be addressed in future research and implementation:1.",
    "Contextual Understanding and Interpretation: Efforts should be focused on enhancing LLM's contextual understanding and improving its ability to provide transparent explanations for its generated responses.",
    "It is important that the data used to train LLM also include a large amount of medical data.",
    "Advancements in natural language processing and explainable AI techniques can contribute to better interpretability, enabling healthcare professionals to trust and validate the model's recommendations [9, 25]. 2.",
    "Collaborative Model Development: Collaboration between AI developers, healthcare professionals, and domain experts is crucial for the successful integration of LLMs in diagnostic medicine."
  ]
}